h3. Issue Summary

When viewing the SLA timer on an JSM issue, the SLA element has inadequate width to show the SLA time in Korean
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a JSM issue with an SLA timer
 # Change language to Korean
 # Open issue and note the SLA timer for certain windows is cut off.

!cutoffSLA.png|width=499,height=314!
h3. Expected Results

SLA timer element should have correct width to support all text.
h3. Actual Results

Part of SLA timer is cut off 
 The cause seems to be the batch.css for the class .sla-tag is too small. It's set to 125px.
{code:java}
.sla-tag {
...
    width: 125px !important;
...
}
{code}
h3. Workaround

You can add custom CSS to overwrite the width of the element in the Jira Announcement Banner
 e.g
{code:java}
<style>
.sla-tag {
    width: 140px !important;
}
</style>
{code}
